  "prompt": "Can I get into the CSE in VIT Chennai at 70+ marks?",
  "response": "The admission criteria for **Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)** at **VIT Chennai** depend on your performance in the **VIT Engineering Entrance Exam (VITEEE)**. Generally, VIT uses a rank-based cutoff system for admissions, and the required cutoff varies each year based on factors like the number of applicants, the difficulty of the exam, and seat availability.\n\nIf you scored **70+ marks in VITEEE**, here\u2019s what you should know:\n\n1. **Cutoff Trends**:\n   - The cutoff for CSE at VIT Chennai is usually higher compared to other branches.\n   - In recent years, aspiring candidates for CSE at VIT Chennai typically needed ranks within the **top 20,000\u201330,000** to secure a seat (depending on category and branch preference).\n\n2. **Marks vs Rank**:\n   - A score of 70+ may or may not guarantee a rank within the eligible range, as the rank depends on the overall performance of all candidates.\n   - If your 70+ score places you within the top **30,000 ranks**, you might have a chance at CSE in VIT Chennai.\n\n3. **Category and Quota**:\n   - The cutoff is lower for **state quota** (Tamil Nadu candidates) compared to the **general category**.\n   - Reserved category candidates (SC/ST/OBC) may have slightly lower cutoffs.\n\n4. **Branch Upgrade Option**:\n   - If you don\u2019t secure CSE directly, you might get a related branch (like IT or CSE with specialization) and apply for a branch upgrade later, subject to availability.\n\n5. **Alternative Options**:\n   - If CSE at VIT Chennai is not possible, consider **VIT Vellore, VIT Bhopal, or VIT AP**, as they sometimes have slightly lower cutoffs for the same branch.\n\n### Advice:\n- Check your **VITEEE rank** once it is announced.\n- Research the **previous year\u2019s cutoff trends** for CSE at VIT Chennai.\n- Be open to applying for **related branches** if CSE is not initially available.\n\nGood luck! Let me know if you need further clarification.",
